WEBVTT

00:01.413 --> 00:04.965
Previously
on "Promised Land"...
The bones.
They're gone.

00:04.965 --> 00:06.137
He must have moved them.

00:06.137 --> 00:07.137
♪♪

00:07.137 --> 00:08.206
Veronica.

00:08.206 --> 00:09.655
You're still dead to me.

00:09.655 --> 00:11.241
♪♪

00:11.241 --> 00:12.241
Oh.

00:12.241 --> 00:13.551
Get out!

00:13.551 --> 00:15.827
I owe you.

00:15.827 --> 00:18.448
It was so much easier
to hate you when you were gone.

00:18.448 --> 00:19.413
How about now?

00:24.965 --> 00:26.931
♪♪

00:26.931 --> 00:28.586
Margaret:
What changed?

00:28.586 --> 00:29.655
Us.

00:29.655 --> 00:33.655
♪♪

00:33.655 --> 00:36.000
Joe: "It was
the best of times..."

00:36.000 --> 00:37.103
Lettie: Uh-huh.

00:37.103 --> 00:39.931
"...it was
the worst of times.

00:39.931 --> 00:41.896
It was the spring
of hope..."

00:41.896 --> 00:43.448
Mm-hmm.

00:43.448 --> 00:46.586
"...it was the winter
of despair."

00:46.586 --> 00:47.620
[ Chuckles ]

00:59.620 --> 01:02.482
♪♪

01:10.275 --> 01:12.034
♪♪

01:20.172 --> 01:24.275
♪♪

01:24.275 --> 01:25.655
I'm sorry.

01:25.655 --> 01:27.620
♪♪

01:38.827 --> 01:40.206
♪♪

01:40.206 --> 01:41.275
ConMargaret?

01:41.275 --> 01:43.344
♪♪

01:43.344 --> 01:44.413
Yes.

01:44.413 --> 01:49.172
♪♪

01:49.172 --> 01:51.172
I like her a lot.

01:51.172 --> 01:53.931
♪♪

01:57.689 --> 01:59.620
Yeah. Vengan.

02:02.034 --> 02:07.034
"We had everything
before us,

02:07.034 --> 02:09.517
we had nothing before us.

02:09.517 --> 02:11.482
♪♪

02:11.482 --> 02:13.206
We were all going
direct to Heaven...

02:13.206 --> 02:15.965
♪♪

02:15.965 --> 02:18.551
...we were all going
direct the other way."

02:18.551 --> 02:25.827
♪♪

02:25.827 --> 02:33.137
♪♪

02:33.137 --> 02:34.482
Joe: Antonio.

02:37.068 --> 02:39.931
You find bones in my vineyard
and you don't tell me?

02:39.931 --> 02:43.517
I have to find out
from Gonzo?

02:43.517 --> 02:44.620
You didn't need me
to tell you

02:44.620 --> 02:47.137
where the bones
were buried.

02:47.137 --> 02:52.413
♪♪

02:52.413 --> 02:54.103
Where'd you find this?

02:54.103 --> 02:55.689
It was with the bones.
That's impossible.

02:55.689 --> 02:58.068
Is it?
Oscar Honeycroft
was a drunk.

02:58.068 --> 02:59.517
He drove his car
off a bridge.

02:59.517 --> 03:01.931
And conveniently for you,
the body was never found.

03:01.931 --> 03:04.206
♪♪

03:04.206 --> 03:06.793
You made it look like
an accident.

03:06.793 --> 03:11.000
You killed him, and then
you took over the vineyard.

03:11.000 --> 03:12.586
Hmm?

03:12.586 --> 03:17.172
♪♪

03:17.172 --> 03:20.034
Why didn't you tell me,
Apá?

03:20.034 --> 03:22.068
I could've kept
your secret.

03:22.068 --> 03:23.931
I did not kill
your grandfather.

03:23.931 --> 03:25.689
No, you just moved the bones
because you're innocent.

03:25.689 --> 03:27.655
I moved the bones because I knew
what people would think.

03:27.655 --> 03:28.689
Yeah.
Can you blame them?

03:28.689 --> 03:30.758
I have nothing to hide.

03:30.758 --> 03:33.862
The truth is, I was about to
call you down here.

03:33.862 --> 03:35.344
I need a lock
of your hair.

03:35.344 --> 03:36.517
For what?

03:36.517 --> 03:37.965
I hired an investigator.

03:37.965 --> 03:39.310
I'm having
the bones tested.

03:39.310 --> 03:41.517
We'll compare the DNA
to yours.

03:41.517 --> 03:47.448
♪♪

03:47.448 --> 03:48.896
And then you'll see,

03:48.896 --> 03:51.000
these aren't
your grandfather's bones.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.034
♪♪

03:53.034 --> 03:56.206
No.

03:56.206 --> 03:58.517
And I'm not a killer.

03:58.517 --> 04:01.655
♪♪

04:01.655 --> 04:04.655
-- Captions by VITAC --

04:04.655 --> 04:07.448
♪♪

04:07.448 --> 04:08.655
[ Sabio's "Nadie Confío" plays ]

04:08.655 --> 04:10.034
♪ Tengo mi flow
de todos los estilos ♪

04:10.034 --> 04:11.896
♪ Llego con diamantes
te dan escalofrios ♪

04:11.896 --> 04:13.689
♪ Cobro por mi risa
no te rías con nadie ♪

04:13.689 --> 04:15.448
♪ Siempre con los míos
y nadie confío ♪

04:15.448 --> 04:18.310
♪ Y nadie confío

04:18.310 --> 04:22.241
Who's the lucky recipient
of all that aggression?

04:22.241 --> 04:24.655
Left's for my father.

04:24.655 --> 04:26.655
Right's for my soon-to-be
ex-husband.

04:26.655 --> 04:29.689
[ Panting ]

04:29.689 --> 04:31.965
And that was for
the custody lawyer I just fired.

04:31.965 --> 04:34.310
Well, hey,
for the next few weeks,

04:34.310 --> 04:36.241
I'm gonna be here
at this time every morning,

04:36.241 --> 04:37.482
if you ever need
a sparring partner.

04:37.482 --> 04:39.379
[ Chuckles ]

04:39.379 --> 04:41.758
[ Inhales sharply ]

04:41.758 --> 04:44.103
Wouldn't want to ruin
that pretty face of yours.

04:44.103 --> 04:46.275
♪ Siempre con los míos
y nadie confío ♪

04:46.275 --> 04:47.793
Alright.

04:47.793 --> 04:49.758
♪ Siempre con los míos
y nadie confío ♪

04:55.000 --> 04:57.310
Pá, someone took
my parking spot.

04:57.310 --> 04:58.482
I gave it to Javier.

04:58.482 --> 05:01.206
You know, since
he actually comes here.

05:01.206 --> 05:03.172
What are you talking about?
I'm here all the time.

05:03.172 --> 05:04.482
Did you see this?

05:04.482 --> 05:06.448
"Latinx Winemakers
Come Into Their Own."

05:06.448 --> 05:08.896
Heritage House
isn't even mentioned.

05:08.896 --> 05:11.965
First, I don't know
what "Latinx" means.

05:11.965 --> 05:13.862
Second, I don't get
what the big deal is.

05:13.862 --> 05:16.758
Pá, you are
the O.G. Latino winemaker.

05:16.758 --> 05:18.068
You are the list.

05:18.068 --> 05:19.586
So how come
you're not on there?

05:19.586 --> 05:20.827
We sell wine
to everybody.

05:20.827 --> 05:22.413
We sell wine
to white people.

05:22.413 --> 05:25.206
A core market that's treated us
very well.

05:25.206 --> 05:27.413
V, help me out here.

05:27.413 --> 05:30.103
I'm trying to tell Papi that
we should reclaim our roots,

05:30.103 --> 05:33.172
put a little heritage
into Heritage House.

05:33.172 --> 05:35.793
There's this woman,
Natalia Rojas.

05:35.793 --> 05:38.551
She's the top Latina
marketing guru in the country.

05:38.551 --> 05:41.551
That Dos Equis campaign?
That was her.

05:41.551 --> 05:43.241
That was
a good campaign.

05:43.241 --> 05:45.448
Okay, look, Latinos are joining
the middle class

05:45.448 --> 05:47.793
in record numbers.

05:47.793 --> 05:49.275
And if we don't jump
on that,

05:49.275 --> 05:51.758
maybe one of
our competitors will.

05:51.758 --> 05:55.034
Plus, Pá,
it's the right thing to do.

05:56.137 --> 05:58.448
Fine. Talk to
your marketing lady.

05:58.448 --> 05:59.896
Oy! Mwah!

05:59.896 --> 06:01.413
Gracias,Papi.

06:01.413 --> 06:03.551
♪♪

06:03.551 --> 06:05.103
[ Chuckles ]

06:05.103 --> 06:06.413
How you doing?
[ Door closes ]

06:06.413 --> 06:08.103
How's Rita?

06:08.103 --> 06:09.827
She misses her dad.

06:09.827 --> 06:11.413
I'm sorry, V.

06:11.413 --> 06:13.344
I had no idea
you and Michael were having

06:13.344 --> 06:15.448
those kinds of problems.

06:15.448 --> 06:18.379
Thought I could handle it
on my own.

06:18.379 --> 06:20.482
And now he wants
joint custody.

06:20.482 --> 06:23.241
Fight it, Veronica,
with everything you've got.

06:23.241 --> 06:25.827
♪♪

06:25.827 --> 06:28.413
[ "Tu Y Las Nubes" playing ]

06:35.413 --> 06:36.241
Oye.

06:46.620 --> 06:49.827
♪ Mi amor está por lo suelos♪

07:16.862 --> 07:18.068
Oye.

07:24.827 --> 07:26.482
♪♪

07:29.241 --> 07:30.448
[ Scoffs ]

07:45.034 --> 07:48.689
♪♪

07:48.689 --> 07:49.862
Mm.

07:49.862 --> 07:56.586
♪♪

07:56.586 --> 07:57.724
Rich Mom:
How about you, Lettie?

07:57.724 --> 07:59.517
Anything for
the charity auction?

07:59.517 --> 08:01.172
Lettie?

08:02.137 --> 08:04.758
Oh. I'm sorry.
[ Chuckles ]

08:04.758 --> 08:08.482
Um, uh...yeah,
I was, uh, thinking...

08:08.482 --> 08:09.862
[ Door opens ]
...for the last item,

08:09.862 --> 08:12.068
maybe we could auction...

08:13.103 --> 08:14.862
Father Ramos?

08:14.862 --> 08:16.413
♪♪

08:16.413 --> 08:20.620
Why, Lettie,
that's not a bad idea.

08:20.620 --> 08:23.000
Dinner with
Father Ramos?

08:23.000 --> 08:24.827
Better yet,
a weekend getaway.

08:24.827 --> 08:27.137
[ Laughter ]

08:27.137 --> 08:34.241
♪♪

08:34.241 --> 08:36.310
They're bored housewives.

08:36.310 --> 08:38.206
We have a history, Billy.

08:38.206 --> 08:40.172
And we're playing
with fire.

08:43.965 --> 08:46.206
And the other night
at the church,

08:46.206 --> 08:49.724
the way I felt with you,
it -- [Sighs]

08:51.206 --> 08:54.068
I need some space, Billy.

08:54.068 --> 08:55.724
Please.

08:55.724 --> 09:01.862
♪♪

09:01.862 --> 09:04.068
I understand.
Yeah.

09:04.068 --> 09:06.275
♪♪

09:06.275 --> 09:07.275
[ Door closes ]

09:07.275 --> 09:09.206
[ Groans ]

09:09.206 --> 09:15.931
♪♪

09:15.931 --> 09:17.517
Excuse me?

09:17.517 --> 09:19.344
The union rep
and his negotiator are here.

09:19.344 --> 09:22.344
Richie! Where's that handsome
son of a bitch?!

09:22.344 --> 09:24.172
Richie, get over here!

09:24.172 --> 09:26.068
How are you, Joe?

09:26.068 --> 09:27.068
Veronica.

09:27.068 --> 09:28.896
Richie,
always a pleasure.

09:28.896 --> 09:30.827
Where's that lawyer of yours,
Cal Peters?

09:30.827 --> 09:32.931
Actually, Joe,
Sacramento brought in

09:32.931 --> 09:34.724
someone new this year.

09:34.724 --> 09:37.172
Say hello to
Tomás Gutierrez.

09:37.172 --> 09:38.862
Tomás, huh?

09:38.862 --> 09:41.137
Latino, even better.

09:41.137 --> 09:43.068
Joe Sandoval.
Un placer.

09:43.068 --> 09:44.517
This is my daughter,
Veronica.

09:44.517 --> 09:46.448
She'll be handling
negotiations.

09:46.448 --> 09:49.068
Which I trust will go as
smoothly as they always have.

09:49.068 --> 09:51.517
So, I worked up an offer
to get the ball rolling.

09:51.517 --> 09:55.275
We s-suggest a 3% raise
across the board and --

09:55.275 --> 09:57.517
Well, 3% seems
pretty meager,

09:57.517 --> 10:00.379
especially with inflation
at 6%.

10:00.379 --> 10:02.620
Yeah, I don't see any provision
for health insurance.

10:02.620 --> 10:04.689
Cost is prohibitive,
as you know.

10:04.689 --> 10:06.413
Not prohibitive for
the mostly white employees

10:06.413 --> 10:09.034
who work
in your tasting room.

10:09.034 --> 10:11.862
Are you insinuating we treat
our Latino workers

10:11.862 --> 10:14.137
differently
than our other employees?

10:14.137 --> 10:16.551
Well, I don't have to
imply it. You do.

10:16.551 --> 10:17.655
Richie, what the hell?

10:17.655 --> 10:18.827
Why don't we all
sit down --

10:18.827 --> 10:21.172
No. We're gonna need to see
a 6% wage increase

10:21.172 --> 10:23.206
and paid medical leave
for all grape workers.

10:23.206 --> 10:24.413
That's for starters.

10:24.413 --> 10:26.448
No grower in the valley
will agree to that.

10:26.448 --> 10:28.724
Well, your stepson Mateo
disagrees.

10:28.724 --> 10:30.862
No successfulgrower.

10:30.862 --> 10:32.586
Papá.

10:32.586 --> 10:34.137
Excuse us, gentlemen.

10:34.137 --> 10:35.655
♪♪

10:35.655 --> 10:38.827
Pá, why don't you let me
try to handle this my way.

10:38.827 --> 10:40.137
Screw this guy.

10:40.137 --> 10:42.896
I know, but you've trusted me
with negotiations before,

10:42.896 --> 10:45.517
and you've been happy
with the result, right?

10:45.517 --> 10:48.137
Take care of it.

10:48.137 --> 10:49.517
I will.

10:49.517 --> 10:50.586
♪♪

10:50.586 --> 10:52.896
Gentlemen.

10:52.896 --> 10:55.517
Heritage House prides itself on
always being at the forefront

10:55.517 --> 10:57.896
of treating its workers
with dignity.

10:57.896 --> 11:00.034
So, if you'll give me
a chance,

11:00.034 --> 11:01.586
I'd love to show you that
never has that been

11:01.586 --> 11:03.724
more true than today.

11:03.724 --> 11:07.931
Great.
In that case...

11:07.931 --> 11:08.965
it's a date.

11:08.965 --> 11:10.862
♪♪

11:18.172 --> 11:21.551
[ Truck approaching ]
♪♪

11:21.551 --> 11:22.586
[ Engine shuts off ]

11:26.379 --> 11:27.551
Manuel.

11:27.551 --> 11:32.586
♪♪

11:56.137 --> 11:58.172
♪♪

12:00.137 --> 12:02.827
♪♪

12:02.827 --> 12:05.620
[ Engine starts ]

12:05.620 --> 12:12.241
♪♪

12:13.965 --> 12:16.413
Nati: I gotta be honest --
I only agreed to this meeting

12:16.413 --> 12:18.275
because someone I used to date
swore by

12:18.275 --> 12:19.448
Heritage House's Sauv Blanc.

12:19.448 --> 12:21.655
Mm. Did you date
a 50-year-old white lady

12:21.655 --> 12:22.965
from Orange County?

12:22.965 --> 12:24.241
'Cause that's why I'm here.

12:24.241 --> 12:26.517
[ Chuckles ]
I'm listening.

12:26.517 --> 12:29.379
Heritage House was snubbed
on a Latinx Tastemakers List.

12:29.379 --> 12:32.275
Literally no mention,
when my father was the pioneer

12:32.275 --> 12:34.448
Latino winemaker in Sonoma.

12:34.448 --> 12:36.517
I want to sell
to people like us.

12:36.517 --> 12:39.862
I want Heritage House to mean
something to people like us.

12:39.862 --> 12:41.862
You have an idea?

12:41.862 --> 12:43.827
A high-end tasting event.

12:43.827 --> 12:47.275
We bring in an elite group
of Mexican chefs, sommeliers,

12:47.275 --> 12:49.482
food writers --
no one over 40.

12:49.482 --> 12:51.172
Get people to start thinking
about the label

12:51.172 --> 12:52.241
in a whole new way.

12:52.241 --> 12:53.827
"We're not your father's
Heritage House."

12:53.827 --> 12:56.482
Yeah, I -- I like it.
I do.

12:56.482 --> 12:58.413
Uh, but if you don't
mind me asking,

12:58.413 --> 13:03.000
why are you thinking so small?
You know?

13:06.241 --> 13:08.379
Perothe way that
the Latin culture is moving,

13:08.379 --> 13:12.137
these dividing lines,
they mean less and less.

13:12.137 --> 13:14.413
Let's make Heritage House
the standard bearer

13:14.413 --> 13:16.551
para todos Latinos
in the U.S.

13:16.551 --> 13:18.758
We'll do your event,
but let's bring in

13:18.758 --> 13:20.517
the hottest Cuban chef
from Miami,

13:20.517 --> 13:22.965
the New York City sommelier
from Peru.

13:22.965 --> 13:24.379
You know?

13:24.379 --> 13:26.310
Puro Latino.

13:26.310 --> 13:27.586
[ Clicks teeth ]

13:27.586 --> 13:29.379
I knew coming to the best
was the way to go.

13:29.379 --> 13:30.620
[ Chuckles ]

13:31.758 --> 13:35.275
So, all Cal grads scope out
their next target at the gym?

13:35.275 --> 13:37.172
[ Chuckles ]

13:37.172 --> 13:39.965
Like a true Stanford grad,
you've done your homework.

13:39.965 --> 13:42.310
No, it was a coincidence.
I asked your stepbrother, Mateo,

13:42.310 --> 13:44.310
what's a good place to work out
while I'm in town?

13:44.310 --> 13:46.827
Buenos días, Luis.
Señora.

13:46.827 --> 13:48.448
Yeah, my friend's
a labor lawyer.

13:48.448 --> 13:49.931
It's a nomadic life.

13:49.931 --> 13:51.689
This month, grape workers
in Sonoma.

13:51.689 --> 13:53.655
Next month, hotel workers
in Las Vegas.

13:53.655 --> 13:55.206
But I love what I do.

13:55.206 --> 13:57.655
You do, too.
I can tell.

13:57.655 --> 14:00.620
Yeah, well, my family's overcome
a lot to get where they are.

14:00.620 --> 14:02.965
My father started out
in the fields.

14:02.965 --> 14:04.689
And we became the first vineyard
in the valley

14:04.689 --> 14:06.413
to offer
a higher education fund

14:06.413 --> 14:09.034
and paid internships
for high school students.

14:09.034 --> 14:12.206
To start an ESL program
for your workers.

14:12.206 --> 14:14.379
Someone else did
their homework.

14:14.379 --> 14:16.655
Yeah, that was
Lettie's passion project.

14:16.655 --> 14:19.482
It's a shame
it was discontinued.

14:19.482 --> 14:22.034
Look, I don't begrudge
your family's success.
No?

14:22.034 --> 14:24.793
I just think you lost contact
with where you came from.

14:24.793 --> 14:27.241
We're actually hosting
a big Latin networking event

14:27.241 --> 14:28.586
this weekend.

14:28.586 --> 14:31.137
It's my sister's idea.

14:31.137 --> 14:32.620
Why don't you come by.

14:32.620 --> 14:35.793
Come see what us Sandovals
do best --

14:35.793 --> 14:38.413
uplift and connect
with others.

14:38.413 --> 14:40.793
Sounds like
a second date.

14:40.793 --> 14:42.724
That would imply
there was a first.

14:42.724 --> 14:44.172
That's not what this was?

14:44.172 --> 14:45.586
Us? Nah.

14:45.586 --> 14:49.034
If it had been, you wouldn't be
getting a second.

14:49.034 --> 14:50.758
♪♪

14:50.758 --> 14:52.517
I'll see you there.

14:52.517 --> 14:53.586
[ Telephone ringing ]

14:53.586 --> 14:55.172
[ Margaret sighs ]

14:55.172 --> 14:56.724
♪♪

14:56.724 --> 14:58.310
[ Knock on door ]

14:59.241 --> 15:00.689
Antonio!

15:00.689 --> 15:02.172
Come in, come in.

15:02.172 --> 15:03.551
Mwah!

15:05.931 --> 15:07.034
Oh.

15:07.034 --> 15:09.034
Who do I need to kill?

15:09.965 --> 15:11.655
I found the bones.

15:11.655 --> 15:14.000
What?

15:14.000 --> 15:15.275
Where?

15:15.275 --> 15:16.620
Joe took them.

15:16.620 --> 15:18.000
[ Scoffs ]

15:18.000 --> 15:20.034
He said he didn't do it.

15:20.034 --> 15:23.000
He's even getting
them tested.

15:23.000 --> 15:25.172
I guess we'll just wait
and see.

15:30.413 --> 15:32.517
...they were so jealous
of you today.

15:32.517 --> 15:33.517
Mm.

15:33.517 --> 15:35.379
If they only knew

15:35.379 --> 15:38.896
Billy has been looking at you
that way for 30 years.

15:38.896 --> 15:40.896
I think you're forgetting about
my husband, Marta.

15:47.068 --> 15:48.965
Marta.
[ Chuckles ]

15:50.379 --> 15:51.965
Marta.

15:53.310 --> 15:54.724
Marta.

15:58.344 --> 15:59.379
[ Billy whistles ]

16:02.034 --> 16:03.931
Ay.

16:03.931 --> 16:04.965
[ Sighs ]

16:05.482 --> 16:06.275
Lettie?

16:07.172 --> 16:08.206
Lettie!

16:08.206 --> 16:09.206
¿Oye, qué te pasó?

16:13.241 --> 16:14.655
ándale!

16:19.344 --> 16:24.517
♪♪

16:24.517 --> 16:25.931
Gracias.

16:25.931 --> 16:27.379
♪♪

16:27.379 --> 16:28.862
[ Door opens ]

16:28.862 --> 16:30.172
Margaret: Lettie?

16:30.172 --> 16:31.586
Lettie, oh, my God.

16:31.586 --> 16:33.448
I came as soon as I heard.

16:33.448 --> 16:34.482
What do you need?

16:34.482 --> 16:36.689
I'm -- I'm fine.
Really.

16:36.689 --> 16:38.517
I'll bring you
some ice packs.

16:42.896 --> 16:43.793
Vamanos.

16:52.758 --> 16:54.827
Oye,Joe, Billy...

16:57.034 --> 16:58.137
I'm feeling
much better.

17:00.551 --> 17:02.000
ándale.

17:06.068 --> 17:07.517
[ Door slides closed ]

17:07.517 --> 17:08.689
Thank you for coming.

17:08.689 --> 17:10.310
Of course.

17:15.241 --> 17:17.620
♪♪

17:17.620 --> 17:19.551
You've never
been inside before.

17:19.551 --> 17:21.758
♪♪

17:21.758 --> 17:23.724
I see you put
your touch on it.

17:23.724 --> 17:26.896
♪♪

17:26.896 --> 17:29.448
Lettie, it's 100 degrees
out there.

17:29.448 --> 17:31.241
When it's this hot,
you should slow down.

17:31.241 --> 17:33.379
"Slow down"?

17:33.379 --> 17:36.379
Margaret, I don't think you
understand how our jobs work.

17:36.379 --> 17:37.482
Of course I do.

17:37.482 --> 17:38.793
I'm down here with you guys
all the time.

17:38.793 --> 17:40.137
No, you sit in
Gonzo's trailer.

17:40.137 --> 17:42.827
Sometimes.
All the time.

17:42.827 --> 17:44.655
You had a fridge put in
for your colas.

17:44.655 --> 17:48.758
We're out there working all day,
every day.

17:48.758 --> 17:50.034
And I'm young,
and I'm strong,

17:50.034 --> 17:52.241
but there are workers
who are much older than me

17:52.241 --> 17:54.896
doing the same job.

17:54.896 --> 17:58.965
No, I'm sorry,
but you don't understand.

17:58.965 --> 18:01.241
You don't understand
at all.

18:01.241 --> 18:02.862
♪♪

18:02.862 --> 18:04.689
You are feeling better,
aren't you?

18:04.689 --> 18:07.793
♪♪

18:07.793 --> 18:10.103
Joe:
Congratulations, Mateo.

18:11.965 --> 18:14.241
From the year I married
your mother.

18:14.241 --> 18:16.862
Thanks.

18:16.862 --> 18:19.655
How's Daniela?
You must miss her.

18:19.655 --> 18:22.620
I do. I was just talking to her
right now.

18:22.620 --> 18:24.896
I miss her.

18:24.896 --> 18:28.862
But when she comes back,
she'll be here legally.

18:28.862 --> 18:30.586
I don't want her looking
over her shoulder,

18:30.586 --> 18:33.206
always wondering
when she'll lose everything.

18:33.206 --> 18:34.344
It's no way to live.

18:34.344 --> 18:36.413
I want nothing
but the best for her.

18:36.413 --> 18:38.275
And for you, too.

18:38.275 --> 18:40.965
That's why I came to talk to you
about this labor deal.

18:40.965 --> 18:44.206
This guy, Tomás, what he's
asking for is -- is crazy.

18:44.206 --> 18:45.482
And I could absorb it.

18:45.482 --> 18:49.517
Company like yours,
just getting off the ground?

18:49.517 --> 18:52.172
It'll clip your wings just when
you should be taking off.

18:52.172 --> 18:54.241
I don't really care about
the bottom line

18:54.241 --> 18:55.241
like you do, Joe.

18:55.241 --> 18:56.379
This isn't about
the bottom line.

18:56.379 --> 18:58.103
It's about family.

18:58.103 --> 19:00.517
You and Daniela want
to start one, no?

19:00.517 --> 19:04.793
So you need to think
about them now, too.

19:04.793 --> 19:06.344
♪♪

19:06.344 --> 19:08.344
And what about your dream?

19:08.344 --> 19:10.586
That pinot you've always talked
about cultivating?

19:10.586 --> 19:12.172
That'll take capital.

19:12.172 --> 19:15.172
The kind you won't be able
to spend if you sign this deal.

19:17.620 --> 19:21.241
Hey, you owe it to yourself,
Mateo.

19:21.241 --> 19:22.827
And to your future.

19:22.827 --> 19:27.275
♪♪

19:27.275 --> 19:30.275
[ Telephone rings ]

19:31.862 --> 19:34.344
Yes?

19:34.344 --> 19:36.275
I'm sorry, who?

19:36.275 --> 19:42.517
♪♪

19:42.517 --> 19:48.793
♪♪

19:48.793 --> 19:50.413
Can I help you?

19:51.172 --> 19:52.965
Uh...

19:52.965 --> 19:57.068
Um, Carmen told me
about your custody battle.

19:57.068 --> 19:59.689
I-I don't want you to make
the same mistake I did.

19:59.689 --> 20:00.896
Oh. Wow.

20:00.896 --> 20:02.620
You're admitting you made
a mistake.

20:02.620 --> 20:05.103
You must really want something.
What is it?

20:05.103 --> 20:06.827
I want to help.

20:06.827 --> 20:09.551
That's all.
[ Sighs ]

20:09.551 --> 20:11.000
And I've made
a lot of mistakes.

20:11.000 --> 20:13.448
But the one that keeps me up
at night is leaving you.

20:13.448 --> 20:16.344
Well, I'm sure
your five-star hotel in Como

20:16.344 --> 20:18.517
helps with that.

20:18.517 --> 20:21.103
Como is actually opening
in 2023.

20:21.103 --> 20:24.206
Wow. You know,
why do you actually care?

20:24.206 --> 20:25.310
You've never even
met Rita.

20:25.310 --> 20:27.000
Not by choice.

20:29.379 --> 20:32.172
Look, there's a lawyer,
Pamela Fox.

20:32.172 --> 20:33.448
She's the best
that there is.

20:33.448 --> 20:34.517
I know who she is.

20:34.517 --> 20:35.931
She won't take on
a new client.

20:35.931 --> 20:40.379
She will take you.
I called her.

20:40.379 --> 20:41.586
I already have a lawyer.

20:44.310 --> 20:46.241
Is he telling you
that California law

20:46.241 --> 20:48.275
favors the mother?

20:48.275 --> 20:51.310
Because it sure didn't
for me.

20:51.310 --> 20:52.551
Don't you dare.

20:52.551 --> 20:53.758
Don't you dare come here
and pretend

20:53.758 --> 20:55.724
like you gave us
a second thought.

20:55.724 --> 20:58.517
I fought tooth and nail
for you.

20:58.517 --> 21:00.896
Right.

21:00.896 --> 21:03.862
Joe hired
a huge legal team.

21:03.862 --> 21:06.241
They threw every trick
in the book at me.

21:06.241 --> 21:07.862
Threatened to destroy me.

21:07.862 --> 21:09.551
Look, I know that's not
what you've been led to believe

21:09.551 --> 21:12.896
your whole life,
and for that...

21:12.896 --> 21:15.172
♪♪

21:15.172 --> 21:18.241
...I'm sorry.
[ Sighs ]

21:18.241 --> 21:20.551
I should have been here
to tell you the truth.

21:20.551 --> 21:22.758
♪♪

21:22.758 --> 21:24.482
Well, you weren't.

21:24.482 --> 21:25.931
And I will have to
live with that

21:25.931 --> 21:27.482
for the rest of my life.

21:27.482 --> 21:29.931
♪♪

21:29.931 --> 21:32.482
I am so sorry, Veronica.

21:32.482 --> 21:35.344
♪♪

21:35.344 --> 21:38.137
[ Voice breaking ]
I know I...hurt you.

21:38.137 --> 21:42.758
♪♪

21:42.758 --> 21:46.206
And that is something
that a mother should never do.

21:46.206 --> 21:49.344
[ Crying ]
So trust me...

21:49.344 --> 21:54.137
♪♪

21:54.137 --> 21:55.965
...you don't want
the same fate.

21:55.965 --> 21:59.068
♪♪

22:02.275 --> 22:10.206
[ Elastic Bond's "Solo Tu Amor"
plays ]
So, I was thinking,
maybe the wine could go here?

22:10.206 --> 22:11.965
And we could put, like,
these cute little wine labels

22:11.965 --> 22:14.172
so that everyone knows
what -- what they're drinking

22:14.172 --> 22:15.551
and -- and what
it pairs with.

22:15.551 --> 22:17.275
♪ Y no tengo palabras para

22:17.275 --> 22:19.551
Or we could do it
over here?

22:19.551 --> 22:22.344
No, here, definitely.

22:22.344 --> 22:24.758
And with that view?

22:24.758 --> 22:28.068
Let them see what the
First Family of Latinx
winemakers built, right?

22:28.068 --> 22:30.000
Right.
Yeah, of course.

22:30.000 --> 22:32.068
I'm thinking,
after the event,

22:32.068 --> 22:35.000
we send everyone a dozen cases
of Heritage House wine.

22:35.000 --> 22:36.931
You know, let them pass it
around organically.

22:36.931 --> 22:39.310
Sell it in their restaurants,
add it to their lists.

22:39.310 --> 22:41.206
Yeah, a dozen
seems like a lot.

22:41.206 --> 22:45.931
You want to make a splash,
Carmen, you gotta get wet.

22:45.931 --> 22:47.827
Sure, I guess.

22:47.827 --> 22:50.448
I mean, even if it's a failure,
it's a tax write-off, right?

22:50.448 --> 22:52.344
Oh, you think this could be
a failure, huh?

22:52.344 --> 22:54.103
Oh, no, don't take it
in the wrong way.

22:54.103 --> 22:55.689
It's got nothing
to do with you.

22:55.689 --> 22:57.586
Oh, no, I know.

22:57.586 --> 22:59.034
It's got everything
to do with you.

22:59.034 --> 23:01.241
♪ Y sé que pronto sanarán

23:01.241 --> 23:03.448
♪ Las heridas que
llevo en el alma ♪

23:03.448 --> 23:05.448
[ Sighs ] How obvious is it
that the only thing

23:05.448 --> 23:09.034
my family expects me to
accomplish is the perfect tan?

23:09.034 --> 23:12.551
Is that all youexpect to
accomplish?

23:12.551 --> 23:14.413
Hell no.

23:14.413 --> 23:17.724
Then who gives a damn
what your family thinks?

23:17.724 --> 23:19.241
♪ Las heridas que
llevo en el alma ♪

23:19.241 --> 23:20.413
Food.

23:20.413 --> 23:21.827
You had mentioned ceviche
earlier.

23:21.827 --> 23:24.000
I think that's
a terrific idea.

23:24.000 --> 23:26.517
♪ Puedo encontrar

23:26.517 --> 23:28.206
Mateo: You really don't need
to make us a wedding present.

23:28.206 --> 23:29.206
You were there.

23:29.206 --> 23:30.586
That's all that matters.

23:30.586 --> 23:31.793
Too late.

23:31.793 --> 23:34.241
The vision has taken
a life of its own.

23:34.241 --> 23:35.586
[ Chuckles ]

23:35.586 --> 23:37.137
All it needs now is for you
to get lost for a few hours.

23:37.137 --> 23:38.551
Alright. I'm gonna head up
to Briar Creek.

23:38.551 --> 23:40.034
I'll see you
in a little bit.
I'll see you later.

23:41.896 --> 23:43.793
Uh, actually...

23:43.793 --> 23:45.068
do you mind
if I ask you something?

23:45.068 --> 23:50.448
Sort of some, I don't know,
like, father-son advice?

23:50.448 --> 23:55.068
Uh, I saw Joe earlier today,
and, uh, he had some --

23:55.068 --> 23:59.241
some strongly-worded opinions
about this new labor deal.

23:59.241 --> 24:03.413
Strongly-worded?
My brother? Nah.

24:03.413 --> 24:06.241
Yeah, we are nothing alike,
me and him.

24:06.241 --> 24:07.448
But?

24:07.448 --> 24:09.655
But...

24:09.655 --> 24:12.482
I'm thinking he's not
completely off the mark.

24:12.482 --> 24:14.689
You know, I-I'm trying to build
something here.

24:16.620 --> 24:20.448
Mateo, I will forever deny
that I said this,

24:20.448 --> 24:23.344
but I've often wondered
what my life would be like

24:23.344 --> 24:24.620
if I had been
more like Joe.

24:26.206 --> 24:29.137
There's a reason
why he went from being

24:29.137 --> 24:31.482
the least powerful man
in the vineyard

24:31.482 --> 24:34.758
to being
the most powerful.

24:34.758 --> 24:36.827
I was a dreamer.

24:36.827 --> 24:38.758
He was a doer.

24:38.758 --> 24:39.931
But here's the thing.

24:39.931 --> 24:41.103
You're not him.

24:41.103 --> 24:43.379
You're you.

24:43.379 --> 24:45.793
The question you have to ask
yourself now is,

24:45.793 --> 24:47.241
what's your dream?

24:47.241 --> 24:50.482
And what cost are you willing
to pay to achieve it?

25:14.379 --> 25:15.448
Oye.

25:28.862 --> 25:30.068
Hey.

26:11.517 --> 26:19.379
♪♪

26:21.068 --> 26:25.413
♪♪

26:30.034 --> 26:31.551
Wedding present.

26:32.413 --> 26:35.137
I got to say, I always thought
our son's wedding

26:35.137 --> 26:37.034
would be much fancier
than ours.

26:37.034 --> 26:39.275
That's a low bar,
considering our backdrop

26:39.275 --> 26:41.931
was Gonzo's trailer
and your boutonniere

26:41.931 --> 26:44.862
was a twisted grapevine.
[ Chuckles ]

26:44.862 --> 26:47.034
[ Both laugh ]

26:47.034 --> 26:48.103
You're right.

26:48.103 --> 26:49.655
Ours was much fancier.

26:49.655 --> 26:51.551
[ Chuckles ]

26:51.551 --> 26:55.448
♪♪

26:55.448 --> 26:57.655
[ Laughs ]

26:57.655 --> 26:59.655
I was so nervous.

26:59.655 --> 27:01.379
You?

27:01.379 --> 27:04.689
I squeezed your hands
so tight.

27:04.689 --> 27:06.758
I know. I thought
you were gonna break them.

27:06.758 --> 27:12.068
♪♪

27:12.068 --> 27:12.896
And then...

27:14.758 --> 27:17.482
...I kissed you.

27:17.482 --> 27:18.586
Remember that, Lettie?

27:20.379 --> 27:21.413
How could I forget?

27:24.275 --> 27:27.827
I was marrying
the man I love.

27:27.827 --> 27:30.758
Carrying his child.

27:30.758 --> 27:36.241
I remember everything
about that day, every...

27:36.241 --> 27:37.931
detail.

27:39.517 --> 27:42.517
I still carry it
with me.

27:42.517 --> 27:44.448
Here.

27:44.448 --> 27:51.620
♪♪

27:51.620 --> 27:58.827
♪♪

27:58.827 --> 28:00.448
Leticia.

28:02.965 --> 28:09.586
♪♪

28:09.586 --> 28:10.586
No.

28:10.586 --> 28:11.620
Billy.

28:12.862 --> 28:13.758
Billy.

28:18.689 --> 28:21.034
Billy...

28:21.034 --> 28:22.724
No, I shouldn't have come.

28:22.724 --> 28:24.689
♪♪

28:24.689 --> 28:26.482
[ Door closes ]

28:30.965 --> 28:35.206
Rich Mom: So, we're going to
need the key to the side room
where the chairs are.

28:35.206 --> 28:37.172
Father Ramos
would have that.

28:37.172 --> 28:38.241
Where is he?

28:38.241 --> 28:39.862
Lettie?

28:39.862 --> 28:42.103
You must know.

28:42.103 --> 28:43.827
You know, I --
Father Collins:
Good morning, ladies.

28:43.827 --> 28:46.172
Uh, I will be filling in
for Father Ramos

28:46.172 --> 28:47.758
until further notice.

28:47.758 --> 28:48.896
Is he okay?

28:48.896 --> 28:50.827
I wish I knew
how to answer that.

28:50.827 --> 28:52.482
Father Ramos is gone.

28:52.482 --> 28:54.241
He packed his things
and left town.

28:54.241 --> 28:55.551
♪♪

28:55.551 --> 28:57.068
Oh, Billy.

28:57.068 --> 29:00.965
Honeycroft: Well, if it isn't
the knight in shining armor

29:00.965 --> 29:03.758
and the tutor.
Please, please, join us.

29:03.758 --> 29:06.448
Oh, don't mind me.
I collect them.

29:06.448 --> 29:08.793
Old watches and pistols
are my thing.

29:08.793 --> 29:10.896
So, what brings you
up here?

29:10.896 --> 29:13.413
Margaret invite you to tea
or something?

29:13.413 --> 29:17.241
Mr. Honeycroft, sir,

29:17.241 --> 29:21.586
there are...things we'd like
to ask you for.

29:21.586 --> 29:23.827
To do our job better.

29:23.827 --> 29:28.620
Pues...
it won't cost you nothing.

29:28.620 --> 29:31.034
Don't ask for more pay.

29:31.034 --> 29:32.275
Just a water break.

29:34.379 --> 29:35.655
Don't you get one?

29:35.655 --> 29:39.310
Yes, sir, but on the hot days,
it's not enough.

29:39.310 --> 29:40.482
Ah.

29:40.482 --> 29:41.827
The other day,
Lettie fainted.

29:43.413 --> 29:46.379
Joe: Margaret's right,
Mr. Honeycroft.

29:46.379 --> 29:47.758
We need two breaks.

29:49.241 --> 29:52.931
"And it won't
cost me nothing," huh?

29:52.931 --> 29:56.103
Now, you're learning Spanish,
Margaret, huh?

29:56.103 --> 29:59.586
Mm-hmm.
Cómo se dice,
"Time is money"?

29:59.586 --> 30:00.793
Ah.

30:01.965 --> 30:03.000
Pues...

30:03.896 --> 30:07.655
Ah. Sí.

30:07.655 --> 30:09.689
It's a small request,
sir.

30:09.689 --> 30:11.344
A second water break
and a shade tent

30:11.344 --> 30:12.689
on the hottest days.

30:13.931 --> 30:19.310
We're asking you...
nicely, sir.

30:19.310 --> 30:21.551
For the last time.

30:21.551 --> 30:27.862
♪♪

30:27.862 --> 30:29.379
[ Honeycroft inhales sharply ]

30:29.379 --> 30:30.965
Marta, will you please

30:30.965 --> 30:35.379
show Margaret's friends
to the door?

30:35.379 --> 30:39.172
♪♪

30:41.655 --> 30:43.034
Joe, wait!

30:43.931 --> 30:45.275
My father is wrong.

30:46.379 --> 30:47.413
I know he is.

30:47.413 --> 30:48.758
Let me work on him.

30:48.758 --> 30:50.413
I don't know, Margaret.

30:50.413 --> 30:51.689
Hey.

30:51.689 --> 30:53.896
Give me a chance.

30:56.172 --> 31:01.034
♪♪

31:01.034 --> 31:05.862
♪♪

31:05.862 --> 31:06.931
Okay.

31:06.931 --> 31:08.344
Okay.

31:08.344 --> 31:17.310
♪♪

31:17.310 --> 31:20.310
[ Bajofondo and Mala Rodríguez's
"El Andén" plays ]

31:20.310 --> 31:22.620
♪ Uno, uno, uno, dos, dos, dos♪

31:22.620 --> 31:25.206
♪ Uno, dos, uno, uno, dos♪

31:25.206 --> 31:26.931
♪ Uno, uno, uno, uno, dos♪

31:26.931 --> 31:28.724
Thank you.
♪ Porque no voy
a luchar por tu amor♪

31:28.724 --> 31:30.344
♪ Si no tengo na que perder♪

31:30.344 --> 31:31.310
♪ Si no me lo das tu♪

31:31.310 --> 31:32.275
♪ Otro lo hará♪

31:32.275 --> 31:33.655
♪ Y volveré como siempre♪

31:33.655 --> 31:35.517
Underestimated.

31:35.517 --> 31:37.931
What an excellent place
to be.

31:37.931 --> 31:39.931
The look on their faces
is always extra delicious

31:39.931 --> 31:41.862
when they never expect you
to make the game-winning shot.

31:41.862 --> 31:43.241
[ Glasses clink ]

31:43.241 --> 31:44.689
Former pro athlete.
Oh.

31:44.689 --> 31:46.034
Never leaves you.

31:46.034 --> 31:48.034
Let me guess --
volleyball?

31:48.034 --> 31:49.068
Basketball.

31:49.068 --> 31:50.862
Oh, okay.
Point guard, yeah.

31:50.862 --> 31:54.379
I used to play abroad --
Italy and then Spain.

31:54.379 --> 31:55.517
Wow.

31:55.517 --> 31:56.758
The only time I ever left
the country

31:56.758 --> 31:58.620
was to go
to boarding school.

31:58.620 --> 32:01.965
Just trying to picture you
in that uniform.

32:01.965 --> 32:03.517
[ Chuckles ]

32:03.517 --> 32:05.241
Shall we mingle?

32:05.241 --> 32:06.448
Yeah.
Yeah. Let's.

32:06.448 --> 32:08.000
♪ No pienso perder el tren♪

32:08.000 --> 32:10.586
♪ Tengo las palabras mágicas♪

32:10.586 --> 32:12.275
Excuse me, love,
do we have anything stronger?

32:12.275 --> 32:13.896
I heard
from my investigator.

32:13.896 --> 32:15.931
He spoke
to the DNA lab.

32:15.931 --> 32:17.000
And?

32:17.000 --> 32:18.758
We'll have
the results tomorrow.

32:18.758 --> 32:21.103
I can't wait
to put this to bed.

32:21.103 --> 32:22.103
Mateo.

32:22.103 --> 32:24.034
Antonio.

32:24.034 --> 32:25.551
Mateo.

32:25.551 --> 32:27.379
About that
labor contract.

32:27.379 --> 32:28.482
I thought a lot about
what you said.

32:28.482 --> 32:29.517
Mm-hmm.

32:29.517 --> 32:30.965
Decided to sign
the deal.

32:30.965 --> 32:32.965
You're making
a big mistake.

32:32.965 --> 32:35.241
Maybe.

32:35.241 --> 32:37.103
It's the right thing
for me.

32:37.103 --> 32:38.206
Just wanted
to let you know.

32:38.206 --> 32:42.000
♪♪

32:44.000 --> 32:44.827
Mm.

32:49.758 --> 32:52.137
♪ Pero estoy en el andén♪

32:52.137 --> 32:53.137
♪ De aquí no me muevo♪

32:53.137 --> 32:54.689
♪ No pienso perder el tren♪

32:54.689 --> 32:56.758
♪ Tengo las palabras mágicas♪

32:57.896 --> 32:59.793
♪ Papi escúchame♪

33:01.517 --> 33:04.275
You also have to consider
the foliage-to-fruit ratio

33:04.275 --> 33:07.137
and the makeup of the soil --
elevation, sun exposure,

33:07.137 --> 33:08.344
climate.

33:08.344 --> 33:10.310
And, of course,
the right management.

33:10.310 --> 33:12.965
Ooh, the right management
is key.

33:12.965 --> 33:14.034
Margaret.

33:14.034 --> 33:15.482
[ Laughs ]
Joe, Lettie.

33:15.482 --> 33:17.034
You both look amazing,
as always.

33:17.034 --> 33:18.034
Thank you.
So do you.

33:18.034 --> 33:19.965
What are you doing here,
Margaret?

33:19.965 --> 33:21.551
Good question.
Last time I checked,

33:21.551 --> 33:24.586
you weren't a cutting-edge
Latinx tastemaker under 35.

33:24.586 --> 33:26.482
Well, a girl
can dream.

33:26.482 --> 33:28.413
[ Rita laughs ]

33:28.413 --> 33:30.689
You're just
a little bird today, huh?

33:30.689 --> 33:33.000
Oh, my God.

33:33.000 --> 33:34.103
She's beautiful.

33:34.103 --> 33:36.241
Who?

33:36.241 --> 33:37.448
The reason I'm here.

33:37.448 --> 33:38.413
Excuse me.

33:39.482 --> 33:41.103
Hi!

33:41.103 --> 33:43.655
Rita, this is
your grandmother.
[ Laughs ]

33:43.655 --> 33:45.551
Oh, oh.
We will workshop that.

33:45.551 --> 33:47.586
[ Giggles ]
Rita!

33:47.586 --> 33:50.000
Hello!
Say hi.

33:50.000 --> 33:51.413
Veronica.

33:51.413 --> 33:52.931
I hired
your attorney friend.

33:54.517 --> 33:56.137
She's revisiting
our whole strategy.

33:56.137 --> 33:57.965
Thank you.
Oh, my goodness.

33:57.965 --> 33:59.413
No, thank you.

34:01.241 --> 34:02.758
♪♪

34:02.758 --> 34:03.862
Server:
You're welcome.

34:03.862 --> 34:05.758
[ Indistinct conversations ]

34:05.758 --> 34:07.793
♪♪

34:07.793 --> 34:11.344
Hi, bebé! Bebé, ven!
Ven, bebé!

34:11.344 --> 34:13.448
Oh, mi bebé!
Hey, Ma.

34:13.448 --> 34:14.862
[ Slurring ] How do
you like the party?

34:14.862 --> 34:16.068
It's cool, no?

34:16.068 --> 34:17.068
Uh, it's cool.

34:17.068 --> 34:19.206
It's like getting back
to our roots

34:19.206 --> 34:20.827
or something like that.
"Our roots"?

34:20.827 --> 34:23.275
[ Laughing ]
Ay, bebé.

34:23.275 --> 34:24.344
What's so funny?
"Our roots?"

34:24.344 --> 34:26.448
What do you know
about roots?

34:26.448 --> 34:28.965
You were born
in a mansion.

34:28.965 --> 34:32.344
I -- I was born
in a bathtub.

34:32.344 --> 34:34.068
[ Laughs ]

34:37.827 --> 34:38.827
Hey!

34:38.827 --> 34:43.068
...was born in a --
in a barn!

34:43.068 --> 34:44.551
[ Laughing ]
[ Chuckles awkwardly ]

34:44.551 --> 34:45.620
What's wrong?

34:45.620 --> 34:46.862
Joe Sandoval!

34:46.862 --> 34:48.241
She's wasted.

34:48.241 --> 34:49.724
[ Whines mockingly ]

34:49.724 --> 34:52.551
Joe, listen.

34:56.517 --> 34:58.206
Hey.

35:01.137 --> 35:02.241
Okay, Lettie, ven.

35:04.655 --> 35:06.586
[ Glasses clinking ]

35:10.034 --> 35:14.000
I'm Veronica Sandoval, the CEO
of Heritage House Vineyards.

35:14.000 --> 35:17.482
As many of you know,
my father, Joe Sandoval,

35:17.482 --> 35:21.137
was California's
first Latin vineyard owner.

35:21.137 --> 35:22.620
[ Cheers and applause ]
[ Chuckles ]

35:22.620 --> 35:25.655
It's so good to look out
and see so much talent

35:25.655 --> 35:27.310
from the Latin diaspora.

35:27.310 --> 35:28.931
We may be from
different countries,

35:28.931 --> 35:32.379
but we share similar histories
and similar struggles.

35:32.379 --> 35:39.137
And to honor that heritage,
please enjoy, get some wine.

35:39.137 --> 35:40.241
Cheers. Salud.

35:40.241 --> 35:41.241
[ Cheers and applause ]

35:41.241 --> 35:42.862
Salud!
Salud!

35:42.862 --> 35:44.172
Hey, ven.
[ Laughs ]

35:44.172 --> 35:46.241
Hey, I have a question.

35:46.241 --> 35:47.310
Yeah?

35:47.310 --> 35:48.896
How much did
the party cost?

35:48.896 --> 35:51.275
[ Chuckles ]
I'm sorry?

35:51.275 --> 35:55.620
Between the food, the wine,
plane tickets,

35:55.620 --> 35:58.413
I'm thinking
it's at least 200K.

35:58.413 --> 36:00.172
Close?
[ Crowd murmuring ]

36:00.172 --> 36:01.586
Might have been nice
to put that money

36:01.586 --> 36:04.206
towards the modest
wage increases

36:04.206 --> 36:06.965
your Latino workers
have asked you for.

36:06.965 --> 36:10.241
In honor of your...
"similar struggle."

36:10.241 --> 36:13.620
♪♪

36:13.620 --> 36:15.068
You'll excuse me.

36:15.068 --> 36:16.965
♪♪

36:16.965 --> 36:18.724
Oh.

36:18.724 --> 36:21.482
Hey, I like him.
I like him a lot.

36:21.482 --> 36:23.586
Come back!

36:23.586 --> 36:24.862
Come back!

36:29.068 --> 36:33.448
And Alberto,
the Dominican chef?
He rejected all of
his cases of wine.

36:33.448 --> 36:34.896
Who rejects free wine?

36:34.896 --> 36:36.931
Your event was great,
Carmen, okay?

36:36.931 --> 36:39.000
Yeah.
Till the grand finale.

36:39.000 --> 36:40.275
No, unh-unh.

36:40.275 --> 36:41.758
That was your father
and your sister stepping in it.

36:41.758 --> 36:42.931
That wasn't you.

36:42.931 --> 36:45.068
You created something
from nothing.

36:45.068 --> 36:47.896
You gave people a space
to connect...
Mnh.

36:47.896 --> 36:50.344
...and now they're familiar
with two new brands.

36:51.344 --> 36:53.137
Heritage House?

36:53.137 --> 36:55.000
And Carmen Sandoval.

36:55.000 --> 36:56.275
[ Scoffs ]

36:57.827 --> 36:59.827
Look, you're bored,
Carmen, okay?

36:59.827 --> 37:01.931
And like me, you're no good
when you're bored.

37:01.931 --> 37:04.931
You have to stop limiting
yourself to your family's world.

37:04.931 --> 37:08.068
I mean, they're all about wine,
and you're --

37:08.068 --> 37:10.206
you're meant for more.

37:10.206 --> 37:11.241
Like what?

37:11.241 --> 37:14.068
♪♪

37:14.068 --> 37:19.413
For starters, uh,
dinner, with me.

37:19.413 --> 37:21.068
And then, world domination
or something like that,

37:21.068 --> 37:22.551
but we've got time
to figure it out.

37:22.551 --> 37:23.931
♪♪

37:23.931 --> 37:27.758
Like, a --
Like, a work dinner?

37:27.758 --> 37:29.137
I hate work dinners.

37:29.137 --> 37:35.965
♪♪

37:35.965 --> 37:38.137
Richie: Veronica.

37:38.137 --> 37:40.793
Good to see you again.

37:40.793 --> 37:43.655
Is Joe in this morning?

37:43.655 --> 37:45.241
Nope.

37:45.241 --> 37:46.689
You get me.

37:46.689 --> 37:48.482
The union's counter.

37:49.517 --> 37:51.586
Take all the time
that you need.

37:51.586 --> 37:53.241
We're open
to negotiating.

37:57.931 --> 38:00.206
You know, I, uh...

38:00.206 --> 38:02.655
I clean up nice, but...

38:02.655 --> 38:04.793
I still don't know how to act
at these fancy events.

38:07.000 --> 38:08.896
You want to punch me
with your left or your right?

38:10.517 --> 38:13.034
Physical violence
is for the weak.

38:13.034 --> 38:14.965
Or men.

38:14.965 --> 38:16.620
I tried to handle things
privately with you.

38:16.620 --> 38:18.758
Clearly, that was too much
of an ask.

38:18.758 --> 38:20.827
Veronica --
So -- I'm speaking.

38:20.827 --> 38:22.310
♪♪

38:22.310 --> 38:27.517
You made assumptions, Tomás --
about me, about my family.

38:27.517 --> 38:28.931
When the truth is,
you know nothing

38:28.931 --> 38:32.206
about either of those.

38:32.206 --> 38:34.862
So you want to
negotiate?

38:34.862 --> 38:40.896
♪♪

38:40.896 --> 38:43.068
[ Paper tearing ]

38:43.068 --> 38:47.275
♪♪

38:47.275 --> 38:49.103
That's me negotiating.

38:49.103 --> 38:57.793
♪♪

38:57.793 --> 38:59.931
[ Vehicle approaches ]

38:59.931 --> 39:05.517
♪♪

39:05.517 --> 39:11.172
♪♪

39:11.172 --> 39:13.034
[ Car door closes ]

39:13.034 --> 39:14.206
[ Car alarm activates ]

39:14.206 --> 39:19.241
♪♪

39:19.241 --> 39:20.241
Well?

39:20.241 --> 39:21.965
I want us
to trust each other.

39:21.965 --> 39:23.965
That means everything
to me.

39:23.965 --> 39:25.517
♪♪

39:25.517 --> 39:27.413
Can we open this
together?

39:27.413 --> 39:36.482
♪♪

39:36.482 --> 39:39.103
Lettie: All we want is to feel
valued and like we matter.

39:39.103 --> 39:42.724
Of course you matter.
I thought we were friends.

39:42.724 --> 39:44.586
We are.

39:44.586 --> 39:46.689
But I'm no better
than any other worker.

39:46.689 --> 39:48.896
I didn't say you were.

39:48.896 --> 39:51.379
Look, I asked you
up here for a reason,

39:51.379 --> 39:53.793
and it wasn't
to talk about work.

39:53.793 --> 39:56.206
It was to talk about Joe.

39:56.206 --> 39:57.827
Joe.

39:57.827 --> 39:59.827
Don't act surprised.

39:59.827 --> 40:01.344
I know you're in love
with him.

40:04.310 --> 40:07.310
That's...

40:07.310 --> 40:09.379
I'm in love with Billy.

40:09.379 --> 40:11.689
You love both of them.

40:11.689 --> 40:13.551
I know.

40:13.551 --> 40:15.896
But I love Joe,
and...

40:15.896 --> 40:18.103
I don't want that
to come between us.

40:20.862 --> 40:22.689
You're no good for him.

40:22.689 --> 40:26.000
Excuse me?

40:26.000 --> 40:29.241
You and Joe,
you're very different.

40:29.241 --> 40:31.689
We're more alike
than you think.

40:31.689 --> 40:33.275
More alike
than you two are.

40:33.275 --> 40:35.344
[ Glass shatters in distance ]
[ Gasps ]

40:35.344 --> 40:37.137
[ Crashing ]

40:37.137 --> 40:39.275
Your father?

40:39.275 --> 40:40.931
He's in Santa Paula.

40:40.931 --> 40:42.448
♪♪

40:42.448 --> 40:43.517
[ Clattering ]

40:43.517 --> 40:45.689
Oye.
What?

40:45.689 --> 40:47.586
Margaret, wait.
Come on.

40:47.586 --> 40:50.517
[ Clattering ]

40:50.517 --> 40:52.034
[ Drawer opens ]

40:52.034 --> 40:57.241
♪♪

40:57.241 --> 41:02.517
♪♪

41:02.517 --> 41:03.689
[ Whispers ] No.

41:03.689 --> 41:07.655
♪♪

41:07.655 --> 41:10.137
[ Drawer rattles ]

41:10.137 --> 41:11.758
No.
What are you doing?

41:11.758 --> 41:13.275
Nobody steals
from a Honeycroft.

41:13.275 --> 41:14.620
Don't be stupid.

41:14.620 --> 41:15.655
[ Both scream ]

41:15.655 --> 41:18.586
Shh! Shh!
Shh, shh, shh!

41:18.586 --> 41:20.310
Shh, shh, shh, shh!
Shh!

41:20.310 --> 41:21.448
No, no.

41:22.862 --> 41:24.724
No!
[ Girls screaming ]

41:24.724 --> 41:26.241
[ Gun clatters ]

41:26.241 --> 41:31.551
♪♪

41:31.551 --> 41:33.448
[ Screaming ]

41:33.448 --> 41:35.448
No! No!
Shh! Shh, shh!

41:35.448 --> 41:37.586
♪♪

41:37.586 --> 41:39.000
[ Gunshot ]

41:41.172 --> 41:44.172
[ Groaning ]

41:44.172 --> 41:45.655
[ Girls sobbing ]

41:48.000 --> 41:50.689
♪♪

41:50.689 --> 41:52.034
[ Man moans ]

41:53.448 --> 41:55.275
The bones in
the vineyard...

41:55.275 --> 41:57.034
♪♪

41:57.034 --> 41:59.310
...they are
my grandfather's.

41:59.310 --> 42:01.068
That's impossible.

42:01.068 --> 42:02.172
It wasn't Honeycroft, Apá.

42:02.172 --> 42:03.241
[ Vicente Fernández's "El Rey"
plays ]

42:03.241 --> 42:05.275
♪ Yo sé bien que estoy afuera♪

42:05.275 --> 42:07.758
♪ Pero el día que yo me muera♪

42:07.758 --> 42:08.827
[ Girls sobbing ]

42:08.827 --> 42:10.724
♪ Sé que tendrás que llorar♪

42:10.724 --> 42:13.310
♪ Llorar y llorar♪
Lettie: No, no, no, no, no!

42:13.310 --> 42:15.862
♪ Llorar y llorar♪

42:15.862 --> 42:17.379
♪ Dirás que no me quisiste♪

42:17.379 --> 42:18.586
It was your father.

42:18.586 --> 42:21.586
♪ Pero vas a estar muy triste♪

42:21.586 --> 42:23.034
♪ Y así te me vas a quedar♪

42:27.586 --> 42:37.068
♪♪

42:37.068 --> 42:46.586
♪♪

42:46.586 --> 42:56.068
♪♪
